Reports unresolved references in MongoDB and JavaScript code.
<p>Example:</p>
<pre><code>db
use foo
  -- a reference to a non-existing collection
db.non_existing_collection
db['non_existing_collection']
db['non_existing_collection'].find().hasNext()</code></pre>
<p>The <code>non_existing_collection</code> collection does not exist in the database and will be reported.</p>
